modules.description: This module defines and manages sorting orders for performance measurements, specifically supporting increasing and decreasing order types. It provides functions to compare values based on these orders, along with a hash table mapping string labels to order types. It is used to dynamically select sorting behavior when analyzing benchmark results.

This module renders performance analysis data into terminal images using Notty. It provides functions to generate images from regression results, compare best and worst cases, and format headers and fields for display. It works with hashtables of regression models, result sets, and terminal rectangles to visualize benchmarking data directly in the terminal.

This module maps performance measurement units to string representations, providing functions to associate labels with units, retrieve units by label, and render labels as Notty images. It works with strings, hashtables, and Notty images, primarily supporting the display and categorization of benchmarking metrics. It is used to format and visualize units like "ms" or "bytes" in terminal-based performance reports.

This module renders benchmarking results and OLS analysis data into terminal-friendly images using Notty. It provides functions to generate images from benchmark headers, OLS fields, and sorted OLS results, supporting customizable display of performance metrics. Use cases include visualizing benchmark comparisons and regression analysis directly in the terminal.
